SIMPLE: allophone
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: allophone
<hw>allophone</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>any one of two or more speech
sounds that considered variants of the same phoneme. <as>For example,
the <it>p</it> sounds of <it>pin</it> and <it>spin</it> are
<ex>allophones</ex> of <it>p</it>; and the <it>t</it> sounds of
<it>toe</it> <it>stop</it> and <it>catnip</it> are <ex>allophones</ex>
of <it>t</it></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>allophonic</ent>⟦br⟧
